---
import SectionWrapper from '../SectionWrapper.astro';
import Button from '../Button.astro';
---
<SectionWrapper id="guide" theme="light">
  <!-- Section label -->
  <p class="section-label section-label--light">// 04 YOUR GUIDE</p>

  <!-- Headline -->
  <h2 class="guide-headline">I diagnose before I build. Every time.</h2>

  <!-- Empathy copy -->
  <div class="guide-body" data-animate>
    <p>
      I know what it's like to hand someone your card, watch them visit your
      site later, and feel the conversation go cold. The problem wasn't that
      they weren't interested. The site just didn't carry the weight of the
      conversation.
    </p>

    <p>
      Every client I've worked with had the same pattern. Strong work. Loyal
      clients. A site that was built for the version of the business that
      existed a few years ago. Strangers couldn't bridge the gap. The business
      looked smaller than it was.
    </p>

    <p class="guide-emphasis">That's the gap I close.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Authority copy -->
  <div class="guide-authority" data-animate>
    <p>
      Before any code is written, I produce a Problem Statement. It's a
      plain-language document that defines exactly what's broken and what the
      fix looks like. You read it. You verify it. You sign off. Then I build.
    </p>

    <p>
      One person handles your project from discovery to launch. No handoffs.
      No "the other person had that file." No explaining your business twice.
      When it ships, you get a Handoff Package: your code, your credentials,
      your documentation. Everything you need to run the system without me.
    </p>

    <p>
      If you never call me again after launch, that's a win. That's what the
      Handoff Package is for.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Closing -->
  <p class="guide-closing">// That's Maximum Execution, based in Richmond, Virginia.</p>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <div class="guide-cta">
    <Button variant="primary" href="#diagnostic">[START YOUR PROJECT &gt;]</Button>
  </div>
</SectionWrapper>

<style>
  /* Headline - Geist Sans */
  .guide-headline {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--step-4);
    line-height: 1.15;
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-snug);
    color: var(--text);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-10);
    max-width: var(--measure-wide);
  }

  /* Empathy body copy */
  .guide-body {
    max-width: var(--measure-normal);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-10);
  }

  .guide-body p {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--step-0);
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
  }

  .guide-body p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .guide-emphasis {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text) !important;
    font-size: var(--step-1) !important;
  }

  /* Authority copy */
  .guide-authority {
    max-width: var(--measure-normal);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-10);
    padding-top: var(--space-10);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-muted);
  }

  .guide-authority p {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--step-0);
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
  }

  .guide-authority p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* Closing line */
  .guide-closing {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--step--2);
    color: var(--text-muted);
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
  }

  /* CTA area */
  .guide-cta {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-6);
  }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .guide-headline {
      font-size: var(--step-3);
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .guide-headline {
      font-size: var(--step-2);
    }
  }
</style>
